text: Rahul Shah (born 3 January 1997) is an Indian cricketer. He started playing in List A cricket for Gujarat. He did this during the 2017–18 Vijay Hazare Trophy on 11 February 2018. He started playing first-class cricket for Gujarat in the 2018–19 Ranji Trophy on 15 January 2019. He started playing in Twenty20 on 4 November 2021. In Twenty20, he played for Gujarat in the 2021–22 Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy. ==References== Category:1997 births Category:Living people Category:Indian cricketers
